<p>This User Manual will help you get the most out of OpenGeo Suite.</p>

<p><a href="http://suite.opengeo.org/opengeo-docs/installation/index.html#installation">Installation</a></p>

<p>Install OpenGeo Suite for your platform.</p>

<h3>OpenGeo Suite for Red Hat</h3>

<ul>
	<li>
	<p>New installation</p>

	<ul>
		<li>
		<p>&nbsp;Add the OpenGeo repository by creating the file&nbsp;/etc/yum.repos.d/OpenGeo.repo with the following contents:</p>

		<pre>
[opengeo]
name=opengeo
baseurl=http://yum.opengeo.org/suite/v4/&lt;OS&gt;/$releasever/$basearch
enabled=1
gpgcheck=0
</pre>

		<p>Replace&nbsp; with one of &ldquo;fedora&rdquo;, &ldquo;centos&rdquo;, or &ldquo;rhel&rdquo; based on the distribution.</p>
		Me: or use below command to do the same thing:

		<pre>
curl -o /etc/yum.repos.d/OpenGeo.repo http://yum.opengeo.org/suite/v4/centos/6/x86_64/OpenGeo.repo</pre>
		</li>
		<li>
		<p>Search for OpenGeo packages:</p>

		<pre>
yum search opengeo
</pre>

		<p>If the search command does not return any results, the repository was not added properly. Examine the output of the search command for any errors.</p>
		</li>
		<li>
		<p>Install:</p>

		<pre>
yum install opengeo</pre>
		</li>
	</ul>
	</li>
</ul>
